            "answer_text": " Ben Franklin.  He was a well-known polymath even before the founding of the U.S.  He authored best selling books, owned a very successful publishing business, invented various printing processes - including the security measures for paper money that is still in use today.  He was a very successful entrepreneur, political theorist, politician, diplomat, and a scientist.  His scientific achievements include discovering the property of lightning, numerical methods of population studies, pattern analysis of North Atlantic Oceanic currents, wave theory of light, meteorology, principle of refrigeration, temperature's effect on conductivity, and others.His inventions include lightning rod, bifocal lens, glass armonica, and Franklin stove. He was also an excellent chess player, expert string player (harp, violin, guitar) and composed music (string quartet).  His chess skills were so high, he had to be in England or France to find stronger players, he was the first American chess player known in Europe by name.  Unfortunately, there are no surviving records of Ben Franklin's chess plays, so we cannot know his precise level of play.  He was also a member of committee of Five that drafted the Declaration of Independence.Suffice to say, Ben Franklin was an intellectual bad ass. ",
