            "answer_text": "Alexander Hamilton. He was, apparently, the only founding father that saw America as a nation with a diverse economy, large cities, and sprawling industry. The rest saw it as an agrarian society full of farmers, and it was this that made them fight Hamilton's ideas for a national bank, which was necessary to collect taxes for large public projects (such as future wars) and to print paper money. Our currency system was a crap shoot before that. They also fought him on his idea that the federal government should assume state debts to make American credit competitive abroad, and all of this was absolutely necessary for our survival. Without him and his incredible forethought we'd look more like North Korea than the United States of America that we know today. Or, more likely, some other superpower would've taken our land from us by now.  ",
