            "answer_text": "I will argue against conventional wisdom and champion George Washington. Just read his farewell address from 1797 and see how his warnings about partisanship leading to demagogic tyranny and factionalism facilitating foreign influence over our government correspond to our present troubles with Trump and Russia. He was more prescient than Nostradamus could ever hope to be and his intellectual genius was not limited to the battlefield as many people assume, although his strategic ability alone and his Fabian-like logistical endurance against overwhelming odds perhaps merits him the mantle of \u201csmartest founding father\u201d. But each of our first three presidents were unfathomably intelligent in a way that makes me think about Darwinian devolution and the cognitive effects of atmospheric CO2 doubling since 1800. ",
